text: Sana Mir (born 5 January 1986) is a Pakistani cricket commentator and former cricketer who served as a captain of the Pakistan national women's cricket team in ODIs and T20Is. She has led Pakistan to two Gold medals in Asian Games, first in 2010 and then again in 2014. ==References== ==Other websites== * Sana Mir at ESPNcricinfo * Sana Mir at Cricbuzz Category:Pakistani cricketers Category:1986 births Category:Living people
